From bbe9a6fc8ff33a1facfd03d4d8c41968717e209e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Damien Thenot <damien.thenot@vates.tech>
Date: Sun, 15 Mar 2026 17:08:51 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] feat(qcow2): Add QCOW2 support

The QCOW2 support is mainly located in qcow2util but other files needed
a bit of changes to support the new format.

We have a check to see if a QCOW2 is used for coalesce.
In case of coalesce, if a VDI is opened, we can't use qemu-img commit directly because
it would corrupt the chain, we add function get_openers_pid in util.py
to check for openers.
Only add a warning for setParent about openers since the GC in case of migration
would try to setParent while tapdisk was still active but only pause/unpause
the tapdisk after calling setParent to refresh it.
Meaning we ended up not doing the change of parent correctly and the
image would become invalid.
We haven't observed corruption from changing parent and refresh tapdisk
yet so we reverted to not checking opener but we kept a warning in the
logs.
In cleanup.py, we change LVM VDIs to be RW for qemu-img commit to work.

We also add a compute of the size of a cbtlog for LV.
With VHD, the cbtlog LV size was hardcoded to 4MiB.
With QCOW2, the CBT max size can be bigger than this.
This commit the minimum size of the LV to 4MiB but compute the possible size from
the VDI virtual size to ensure we have enough room in case it's bigger.
The behaviour from before would make the creation of the cbtlog fail for bigger
VDI.

Adapt verifyVHDsOnSR for QCOW2 support and rename to verifyVDIsOnSR

Signed-off-by: Damien Thenot <damien.thenot@vates.tech>
